## Overview

The OTP module handles two distinct verification scenarios:

| Scenario | Trigger | Channel | Expiry |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Registration Verification** | On `POST /register` | Email + WhatsApp | 24 hours |
| **OTP Login (Passwordless)** | On `POST /request-otp` | Email **or** WhatsApp | 5 minutes |

All auth endpoints are prefixed with `/api/auth`.

---

## Authentication Strategy

The API supports **two token delivery mechanisms** — use whichever fits your client:

### Option A — HttpOnly Cookie (Recommended for Web)
The server automatically sets a `jwt` cookie on login/register. Your `fetch`/`axios` requests must include `credentials: 'include'`.

```js
fetch('/api/auth/me', {
  credentials: 'include' // <-- sends the cookie automatically
});
```

### Option B — Bearer Token (Recommended for Mobile / SPAs without cookie support)
The token is also returned in the JSON response body as `data.token`. Store it in memory or `localStorage` and pass it as a header:

```js
fetch('/api/auth/me', {
  headers: {
    Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`
  }
});
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Routes marked **🔒 Protected** require a valid JWT. Pass it via cookie (`credentials: 'include'`) or via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.

