## Error Reference

All error responses follow this shape:
```json
{
  "status": "error",
  "message": "Human-readable error description"
}
```

| HTTP Code | Scenario |
|---|---|
| `400` | Missing required fields, code already used, already verified |
| `401` | Missing/invalid/expired JWT token |
| `404` | User not found (for the given email/phone) |
| `500` | Server-side error (check server logs) |

### Common OTP-Specific Errors

| Message | Cause | Solution |
|---|---|---|
| `"Invalid or expired OTP"` | OTP expired (>5 min) or wrong code | Call `request-otp` again to get a fresh OTP |
| `"Invalid or expired verification code"` | Registration code expired (>24 hrs) or wrong code | Re-register or add a resend endpoint |
| `"User not found"` | `identifier` not in DB | Check spelling or prompt user to register |
| `"Email already verified"` | Duplicate call to `verify-email` | Skip to next step in your flow |
| `"Phone already verified"` | Duplicate call to `verify-phone` | Skip to next step in your flow |
